summary: As far as I know Phoebe isn't the showrunner this year or writer cause of a different project. But she has placed it with...
question: As far as I know Phoebe isn't the showrunner this year or writer cause of a different project. But she has placed it with another person who she trusts
answer:
From an article by Express here.

Phoebe Waller-Bridge hasn’t written the script for Killing Eve season two but has stayed on board as Executive Producer and is part of the directing team.

Waller-Bridge brought her signature dark wit to the writing which many fans hope will remain a part of the show for the second run.

The actress and writer hasn’t revealed an exact reason as to why she is not the lead writer anymore but her wealth of upcoming projects suggest an overflowing schedule for the very in-demand creative.”

Taking the helm for season two is Emerald Fennell.

Fennell is a writer and actress bands is best known for her role as Nurse Patsy Mount on Call the Midwife.

Both Fennell and Waller-Bridge previously worked together as writers on Channel 4’s Drifters.

Speaking about season two, President of BBC America Sarah Barnett said: “With Killing Eve, Phoebe Waller-Bridge, Sandra Oh, Jodie Comer and the enormously talented team created something that cut through the noise with the same elegant efficiency as a poisoned hairpin.

“We are filled with excitement and anticipation for the surprises in store as we move into season two.”
